        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions in SQL Server can have performance implications, especially when used in large queries or applied to many rows. They are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower performance compared to set-based operations. However, for small datasets or infrequent use, the performance impact is minimal."
